3/7/00
  Down signal problem:
    When splicing into a channel whose signal is down, if the timeout mode
    is forced switch, we have a problem.  This is because after the forced
    switch, there will be no incoming picture from the new channel
    (signal down), as a result, the last picture from the previous channel
    will be hold by the mux and will never be output be the output task.
    This means the splice indication signal will never be sent out to PPC.
    Eventually the dpi code will trap itself due to video stopped.

  Solution:
    At forced switch, the splicer task generates additions DUMMY PICSTATs
    to the mux.  This will flush the mux so that the last picture from the
    previous channel will be returned and output by the output task, causing
    the splice indication to be sent to PPC.  Those dummy PicStats have a
    unique address (DUMMY_PICSTAT==0) and hence can be detected and dropped
    by the rate conversion task.  Also those pictures have 0 size, avoiding
    rate conversion request and hence no need to send updated picstat to mux.

  The above solution seems to work, but stay problem afterward.


3/8/00
  Zero TP dropping at input:
    Seems there are lots of zero packets in the ads from SeaChange server.
    Modified bufferer task so that zero packets would not even be queued.
    This way we don't need to rely on the statmux to consider on the zero
    packets info, and we don't need to get rid of zero TPs in rate conversion
    task.  Only disadvantage is that the input TPs are not preserved.

  Note: there is a chance that some of the zeros bits in a zero TP belongs to
    part of a VLC or start code.  In this case, dropping a zero TP at input
    would cause data corruption!
  The above approach is dropped!


