  -> dpi 189

  Potential Bug: a problem in rate conversion is found.
  In rate conversion, we remove PidBufs of original picture, and update
  pPicStat->firstTp to points to the next TP after the removal.
  Therefore right after removal of the last TP, the first TP will points
  to the firstTp of the next picture.  If the picture being rate converted
  is the last picture in a channel, the following pictures may be deleted
  by splicer.  As a result, the firstTp of the picture being rate converted
  will be free by splicer and no longer valid.

  To avoid this problem, the new approach does not remove PidBufs of the
  original picture.  Then, when the rate conversion is done, the original
  TPs are removed and new packets inserted in an atomic operation.
  firstTp and lastTp never change and will always pointing to the right TP.
  (Nobody else should touch this picture being RC excepted the rate conversion
  task).

  Need to introduce one global variable curTp to points to the TP being
  read.  A new compilation flag, RC_DEBUG, will be used for this change.

