  BUG: Two indications for the same DPI request sent.
  Reason: forgot to reset videoDone flag in procFgSpliceChan()'s que overflow
          handling.  As a result, if a picture tagged endPicStat is processed
          by the outputTask but latter untagged due to que overflow, the
          videoDone flag remains on, and as a result, at the real splice
          point, if audio turn off is ahead of video, we will have both
          indications from video and audio turn off.
  Fix: reset videoDone flag in procFgSpliceChan().  Care must be taken for
       possible task switching at critical points.
       => dpi 195.
       
